article.headline: Georgia Southern 70, Winstom-Salem 41
article.story: STATESBORO, Ga. (AP) -- Donte Gennie scored 13 points and Jimmy Tobias added 11 to lead Georgia Southern to a 70-41 win over Winston-Salem State on Saturday. Gennie, who went 4-of-8 shooting, scored seven points during the Eagle's 18-2 run in the first half. During a nine minute stretch, Winston-Salem (1-7) was held without a field goal, missing nine straight while committing five turnovers. Georgia Southern (2-2) took a 34-11 lead with two seconds left in the first half on Gennie's bucket. But Jamal Durham's buzzer beater before halftime cut the lead to 21 for Winston-Salem. In the second half, Georgia Southern took a 54-24 lead with 11:38 remaining on Tobias' jumper and led no fewer than 22 points the rest of the way. Louis Graham grabbed nine rebounds and blocked two shots for the Eagles. Dwayne Foreman had six assists. Roy Peake led the Rams with nine points and four assists.
